Not a girl so can't comment on that. Classes are big — approaching 100 in some. If you want individual attention, you'll likely need to go to office hours. All courses are mainly taught by professors. In addition to lectures, some courses have discussion sections taught by TAs. In my experience, definitely collaborative — if you went to a competitive high school, it should be a welcome change. Fairly easy to get a job — last time I checked the average starting salary was around $85k, and many people go to big tech companies. At the end of the day though, you still need to pass the interview to get the job. Upper division CS registration is rough for everyone — you pretty much can't get into the popular electives until your last few semesters because they run out of space quickly.

