None of the female students I knew ever complained about sexism from fellow students or professors. Core classes are huge, upper division depends on how popular they are — smallest upper division class I took was 30 to 40 people. Taught by professors. Collaborative. Lots of people get internships — I had a very mediocre resume (no SWE internships) and still got interviews from companies like Facebook and Google. My peers who had technical internships got even more interviews. WINS is a social thing and won't help with registration. WICS has "meet the professor" type events and even helps with meeting recruiters.

